                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r">f. 1r</locus>: Unidentified prayer.<quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in a secondary hand; the text is abraded and hardly legible.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#1v">ff. 1v-2</locus>r: Protective prayer.<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 1v: በእድጋድ፡ ወሰለለሎነ፡ ዑራኤል፡ ሰዱያልስ፡ ሰሰንያልስ፡ ተማምዖዶሙ፡ መድፍን፡ ድፍን፡ ልበሙ፡ ወእድልም፡ አዕይንቲሆሙ፡ አድከም፡ ኃይሎሙ፡...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Partly illegible, written in a crude hand, similar but not the same as that of Additio 1.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#2v">ff. 2v-3</locus>r: Calendaric note containing feast days of the Evangelists and disciples.<quote xml:lang="gez">ff. 2v: ሠረቀ፡ መስከረም፡ አመ፡ ፩በርተሎሜዎስ፡ ሐዋርያ። ሠረቀ፡ ጥቅምት፡ አመ፡ ፩ወሰኑዩ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ሐዋርያ። አመ፡ ፳ወ፪ሉቃስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ሠረቀ፡ ኅዳር፡ አመ፡ ፲ወ፰ፊልጶስ፡ ሐዋርያ።...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in black ink, in a secondary hand (neat, rounded, upright or slightly left-sloping letters).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#3r">ff. 3r-3</locus>v: Protective prayer (containing ʾasmat?).<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 3r: በቃለ፡ እግዚአብሕር፡ አብ፡ ቆሔት፡ ወልድ፡ ቆሔት፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቆሔት፡ እንዘ፡ ፫፡ ፩ወእንዘ፡ ፩፫ቱ፡ ጺዱመ፡ ልጋመ፡ እሳት፡ አውላልኤል፡ ኀብዕ፡ መለኮት፡ በዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the same hand as Additio 3.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#3v">ff. 3v-4</locus>r: Prayer for women against the pain of childbirth.<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 3v: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ፩አምላክ። ጸሎተ፡ ምሕረት፡ መላእክት፡ ወሰማዕት፡ ወጳጳሳት፡ ወቀሳውስት፡ ወሰዲያቆናተ፡ ዘጸለዩ፡ ዘንተ፡ ጸሎተ፡ ብእንተ፡ ዕፁባት፡ አንስት፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in the same hand as Additio 3.
The prayer invokes the angel Rufaʾel to protect women from pain during labour. It might be the same prayer as in Ms. EMML no. 4730 (fol. 47a).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#4r">f. 4r</locus>: Protective prayer (containing ʾasmat?).<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 4r: በስመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ ግርሙያል፡ ሽርሙያል፡ አናንያል፡ አዘርያል፡ ተንሥአ፡ ማሰያስ፡ ወሲላሶ፡ እንዘ፡ ይቁረጥም፡ እደ፡ ወእግረ፡ ወኵሉ፡ አባለ፡ ሥጋሁ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ዓምደ፡ ሚካል[sic]፡ ዘዮናስ፡ ዘዮናስ፡ ዘዮናስ፡ እንዘ፡ደቁረጥም፡ እደ፡ ወእግረ፡ ወነፋሱ፡ ለገብርከ፡ ዓምደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in a secondary hand in black and red ink.
Prayer with ʾasmat for ʿAmdä Mikāʾel, the owner of the Ms.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#4v">f. 4v</locus>: Salutation for Fanuʾel.<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 4v: ሰላ፡ ለከ፡ ሰዳደ፡ አጋንንት፡ ፋኑኤል፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ እምጽርሑ፡ ከመ፡ ኤይስክዩ፡ ሰብአ፡ እለ፡ ይኔሁ፡ ለጌጋይ፡ዘዘኢአሁ።...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in black and red ink, in the same hand as Additio 3. Cp. ChRep p. 193 (no.49). The abbreviation ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡ is used.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#5v">f. 5v-6</locus>r: Fragment of an unidentified text.<quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The fols. seem to be taken from another, older, Ms. The hand shows older features. The name Takla Hāymānot is given, probably the donor?
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a9">
                           <locus target="#106vb">f. 106vb</locus>: Ownership note(?).<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 106vb: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘ[l.n.]ካኤል፡ እደ [l.n.]ገብረ፡ [l.n.]ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ራሔል፡ ለ [l.n.]ለመ፡ ዓለም</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note, partly illegible, is crudely written by at least two different hands.
From the pieces that are legible we assume, that the book belongs to ʾAmdä Mikāʾel, and that his father’s name is Gabra [l.n.] and his mother’s name is Walatta Rahel.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a10">
                           <locus target="#107v">f. 107v</locus>: salām lä-Fanuʾel.<quote xml:lang="gez">f. 107v: ሰላ፡ ሰላም፡ ነሀብ፡ ለለጌሠሙ፡ ስብሐተ፡ ፋኑኤል፡ ...</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in black and red ink, in the same hand as Additio 3. The prayer is partly illegible.
It might be the continuation of Additio 7.
The abbreviation ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡ is used.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Walda ʾAnanya is written in red in a supplication formula over an erasue, on fol. 50rb.&#xD;
- Ethiopic numerals are crudely written in pencil in the upper margins at the beginnings of quires (starting at quire IX): fols. 63r, 71r, 79, 95.&#xD;
- At the incipit page of Text II (fol. 65vb), a directive concerning the use of the text is written in the upper margin: ከለአተ፡ ድግመ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ኢትህድጉ “Do not forget to read this twice”.&#xD;
- Text has been erased on fol. 107r and a cross has been painted over it.</item>
                     </list>
